0.43.1

Fix panic caused when reviewing posts with no media.
Fix manual ban functionality.

0.43.0

Allow forcing the re-run of migrations which have already been executed.
Add a migration for retrying failed background tasks.
Check a video's audio type and file format when inspecting compatibility.
Show compatibility video in all browsers if present; link to the original file.
Increase maximum upload size to 25 MiB (was 20 MB).
WebSocket reconnect interval changed to 30 sec (was 10 sec).
Fix HTML datetime format, youtube flag, and youtube thumbnail migration regex bugs.
Increase screenshot size to 1920x1080.
Improve pagination link styling.
Allow HEAD requests.
Log warnings for non-error status codes.
Add .mkv and .ts video support.

0.42.0

Simplify error handling, logging and documentation.
Improve messaging to banned users.
Improve JS fetch error handling.
Remove unnecessary threading.
Only apply Chromium video poster JS fix to Chromium browsers.
Disable legacy post routes.
Add IP hash, user agent, and ban expiration information to the User struct.

0.41.0

Use conventional Rust error handling for minimizing panics and notifying users.
Update logging for consistency and clarity.

0.40.0

Improve support for compatibility videos.
Refactor code, splitting it up into submodules and making it more idiomatic.

0.39.0

Take a regular screenshot of the homepage to be embedded on Discord.

0.38.0

Add thorough comments to all source code, enabling documentation.

0.37.0

